1. Download avro-tools.jar. For this tutorial, we are using avro-tools-1.9.2.jar which will be used to generate classes based on schema.
   Download here: https://mirror.olnevhost.net/pub/apache/avro/avro-1.9.2/java/

2. Add avro to the maven and plugins for auto generated classes.

3. Generate schema using SchemaBuilder and save the result to /src/main/avro/user-schema.avsc

4. Copy avro-tools to project root folder
   and generate User class by "java -jar avro-tools-1.9.2.jar compile schema src/main/avro/user-schema.avsc src/main/java/."

5. Serialize Users to disk and deserialize users from disk
   mvn -q exec:java -Dexec.mainClass=com.brian.avro.UserSerializationWithCodeGeneration

6. Serialize/Deserialize without code generation which means that we can do both without auto-generated class User.
   Instead we can use Schema and in this case, we need to use GenericRecord.

Tutorial from : https://avro.apache.org/docs/1.8.1/gettingstartedjava.html